NAME:
ctimer - a timer written in C.

DESCRIPTION:
Ctime tries to be a simple timer written in C. It's messages are displayed
in plain text with the purpose to be more extensible.

INSTALLATION:
To install the program do 'sudo make clean install'
To uninstall it do 'sudo make clean uninstall'



USAGE:
ctimer [OPTIONS]

       -h, --help
              Display the basic usage of ctimer

       -H, --hours VALUE
              Set the hours

       -m, --minutes VALUE
              Set the minutes

       -s, --seconds VALUE
              Set the seconds

       -M, --message "Write a message in double cuotes"
              Set the desired message

       -n, --notify-send
              Redirect the message to 'notify-send'

       -d, --display
              Displays the time in the CLI


